Class RankedComparator<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.microbean.configuration.spi.RankedComparator<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of object to compare
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparator<T>

    public class RankedComparator<T>
extends Object
implements Comparator<T>
    A Comparator that uses a List of Objects to rank other objects for comparison purposes.

    Laird Nelson

      • compare

        public final int compare(T one,
                         T two)
        Compares two objects, returning -1 if one outranks two, 1 if two outranks one, and 0 if the two objects are either ranked equally or their ranks could not be determined.

        This method makes use of the List supplied at construction time for ranking information.

        Non-null objects outrank null objects.

        Specified by:
        compare in interface Comparator<T>
        Parameters:
        one - the first object; may be null
        two - the second object; may be null
        Returns:
        -1 if one outranks two, 1 if two outranks one, and 0 if the two objects are either ranked equally or their ranks could not be determined
        See Also:
        getComparisonObject(Object), RankedComparator(List)

      • getComparisonObject

        protected Object getComparisonObject(T realObject)
        Given an object to be compared, returns the Object that should be used to determine ranking (as determined by the List supplied at construction time).

        This method may return null.

        Overrides of this method may return null.

        The default implementation of this method simply returns the supplied realObject parameter value.

        Parameters:
        realObject - the object to be compared; may be null
        Returns:
        the Object that should be used to determine ranking (as determined by the List supplied at construction time), possibly null
        See Also:
        RankedComparator(List), compare(Object, Object)
